main event: A US Air Force pilot observed two unidentified aerial objects in Tucson, Arizona, traveling at a speed of 700 mph for a duration of 12 seconds.
interesting points: The objects were described as round, like the sun, and appeared to be luminous.
They were approximately 5 times the size of a C-47 aircraft.
The altitude of the objects was estimated to be between 30,000 and 50,000 feet.
The observer, a US Army Air Forces veteran, was deemed reliable and had 15 years of service.
Weather conditions at the time of the sighting were clear with 30 miles visibility.
